task.summary: Consolidating concepts of Execution Context, request and response. Now, there is only an execution context that contains the original request
Adjustment of visitors for the execution context and adding version to processor as well as the execution context.
Introduced the concept of processor counter so we can know how many processors are in flight
Implemented generic loader from a folder.
Integration with RuleEngine for condition evaluation
Adding unit tests to cover when rule engine returns false or throw an error during evaluation of conditiond

Added ability to request cancellation on execution context, effectively terminating a processor chain without marking it in error. Unit tests are not created yet to prove that it entirely works. Current unit tests aren't broken
First unit test for request cancellation
Changed ExecutionContext object to derive from ServiceResponse instead of ServiceMessage
